    "introduction": "![An image of my finished curd balls](/pix/quarkbaellchen.webp) \u201cQuark\u201d is a type of fresh dairy product. It's usually translated as curd cheese or cottage cheese.",
    "ingredients_source_text": "- 420ml quark (plain yoghurt can be used as a replacement) - 2 eggs - 6 or 7 tbsp of sugar - 2 packets of vanilla sugar - 400g flour (500g if using yoghurt) - 2 packets of baking powder - 1L sunflower oil for frying - (Optional) icing sugar - (Optional) Alcohol by eye so that they do not soak up so much oil",
    "directions_source_text": "1. Mix ingredients (quark, eggs, sugar, flour, baking powder) in one bowl. 2. Pour the sunflower oil into a cooking pot and heat up the hotplate 3. Form balls from the dough and put them into the cooking pot 4. Once they are brown-ish, put them onto a plate 5. (Optional) add icing sugar 6. Enjoy!"
